Titulo: Dua Lipa: Tiny Desk Concert
Descricao: Stephen Thompson | October 25, 2024When Dua Lipa came to visit the Tiny Desk, she had nothing to prove â€” and much to live up to. After all, the singerâ€™s Tiny Desk (home) concert, recorded in London in the aftermath of her 2020 blockbuster Future Nostalgia, still holds the record for the most-viewed Tiny Desk concert in history, her 130 million views surpassing even the likes of Mac Miller and Anderson .Paak. Four years later, the pop superstar finally graced the actual Tiny Desk, this time armed with four warm and inviting songs from Radical Optimism. Arriving in the first half of this year â€” when the dominant storylines in music so often revolved around grievances and rivalries â€” Radical Optimism stood out for its comparatively sunny and forgiving takes on failed and failing relationships, seduction, new love and old wounds. And, of course, it dispensed a world-beating banger in â€œHoudini,â€ which joins past Dua Lipa classics (â€œNew Rules,â€ â€œLevitating,â€ â€œDonâ€™t Start Nowâ€) on her own personal Mount Rushmore.Befitting an artist whose newest songs often reflect the pursuit of personal growth â€” see: â€œHappy for Youâ€ â€” Lipa and her team breezed through the NPR Music offices with a mix of low-drama professionalism and unmistakable warmth.
